# Open-in-installed-app prompt

Full doc: [docs/pwa-open-in-app.md](../../docs/pwa-open-in-app.md).

The bottom dock that nudges mobile-browser members to open the installed PWA is
easy to break silently. Protect these invariants:

- On member tab routes (`/today`, `/leaderboard`, `/activity`, `/group`,
  `/settings`) a fixed bottom nav is shown. The dock MUST be offset above it via
  `bottom-[var(--bottom-nav-height)]`, or its buttons render behind the nav and
  become untappable (the text still shows, so it looks like the button vanished).
- The source of truth is `PWA_OPEN_APP_PROMPT_BOTTOM_NAV_PATHS` /
  `pwaOpenAppPromptSitsAboveBottomNav()` in `src/lib/pwaOpenAppPrompt.ts`. Add
  any new bottom-nav route there — do not hardcode path lists in the component.
- Android cannot auto-launch the installed WebAPK from an in-tab Chrome session.
  Primary CTA is honest home-screen steps (**Got it — I'll use the home screen
  icon**). Optional **Try open in app anyway** uses an intent without
  `S.browser_fallback_url` (never a primary https/`web+` link that reloads the
  tab). Do not restore a misleading primary **Open in app** auto-launch button.
- iOS shows honest home-screen steps with no fake open button.

Before finishing any change to these files, run `npm test` and keep
`tests/unit/pwaOpenAppPrompt.test.ts` green (it guards dock placement and
visibility, including on `/today`).
